-- Colombian Public Credit Director Suarez Quits
-- B y   A n d r e a   J a r a m i l l o
-- 2013-02-25T14:09:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-25/colombian-public-credit-director-suarez-quits-1-.html
Colombia’s Director of Public Credit
Maria Fernanda Suarez said today she’ll leave the finance
ministry for “strictly personal reasons.”  Suarez said in a phone interview she doesn’t have a set
date for her departure, and doesn’t know who will replace her at
the ministry.  Before joining the finance ministry, Suarez, 38, was Chief
Investment Officer at AFP Porvenir, Grupo Aval Acciones y
Valores’ pension fund.  She has also worked in the fixed income
departments of Bank of America Corp., Citigroup Inc., ABN Amro,
and Banco Santander SA.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrea Jaramillo in Bogota at 
 ajaramillo1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Matthew Bristow at 
 mbristow5@bloomberg.net  